description:
Grows almost everywhere around here but mostly in sandy "pine tree humus"/top soil under pine trees, kind of in clusters but each leaf pops out of the soil "on its own", not arranged together in (eg) a rosette.
They have long single-strand, sideways-spreading roots from which the single leafs emerge, looks like it is forming a shallow-rooted network.
(Possibly also have bulbs(?) attached to the root strands, but not sure if the bulbs are truly from that plant, as i haven't found them in every area where they are growing. See 2nd picture for roots + bulb. I've seen many more of the bulbs in other situations, in yet others not a single one. Might be from another plant or from different life/maturity stage I'm guessing)
